# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js application that demonstrates view transitions between different pages. The project uses:
- Next.js with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- View Transitions API

## Key Files and Directories

- [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Main landing page with grid layout and view transitions
- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component
- [app/animations.module.css](mdc:app/animations.module.css) - CSS animations and transitions
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind configuration

## Project Pages

The application consists of three main sections:
1. Code section (/code)
2. Karaoke section (/karaoke)
3. Cocktails section (/cocktails)

Each section uses view transitions for smooth navigation and visual effects.
